From: Mingcong Bai <jeffbai@aosc.io>
Date: Wed, 19 Nov 2025 19:05:09 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 54/74] FEDORA: hplip: C99 compatibility fixes (hpaio.c)

scam/sane/hpaio.c: Include orblite.h for more function prototypes

Otherwise the build fails with compilers which do not support
implicit function declarations.

Submitted upstream: <https://bugs.launchpad.net/hplip/+bug/1997875>

Signed-off-by: Florian Weimer <fweimer@redhat.com>

Link: https://src.fedoraproject.org/rpms/hplip/blob/bbb19dff5e32c47720b7523412dd7a59112a19a3/f/hplip-scan-hpaio-include.patch
Signed-off-by: Mingcong Bai <jeffbai@aosc.io>
---
 scan/sane/hpaio.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/scan/sane/hpaio.c b/scan/sane/hpaio.c
index d342626..57d1dde 100644
--- a/scan/sane/hpaio.c
+++ b/scan/sane/hpaio.c
@@ -50,6 +50,7 @@
 #include "sclpml.h"
 #include "escl.h"
 #include "io.h"
+#include "orblite.h"
 #include "orblitei.h"
 
 
